# Cursor rules for coder-system

This repo follows a cross-agent contract defined in [`AGENTS.md`](../../AGENTS.md)
at the repository root.

**Read `AGENTS.md` before editing anything in this repo.** It defines the
hard rules for frontmatter, registries, ADR append-only semantics, design
lifecycle, numbering, and cross-link integrity.

This `.mdc` file is intentionally a thin pointer. The single source of truth
for agent behavior in this repo lives in `AGENTS.md` so that Claude Code,
Cursor, and any future agent obey the same rules.
